<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Palestinian, Israeli Officials Meet in Athens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian and Israeli
officials began here Thursday their fourth meeting sponsored by
Greece in order to foster a climate of trust and seek viable and
lasting solutions to the Mideast problem.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian delegation was led by Faisal Al-Husseini, who
is responsible for the Jerusalem issues while the Israeli
officials include Minister to the Prime Minister's office Haim
Ramon and former Israeli Prime Minister Shimon Peres.
</P>
<P>
During the four-day meeting, both sides are expected to decide
to create three bipartizan committees such as the
inter-parliamentary committee, the conflict resolution committee
dealing with issues of daily life and the committee to deal with
economic issues.
</P>
<P>
Greece, which is playing an important role in building
confidence between the two sides, is expected to propose the
establishment of two more committees on the protection of cultural
heritage and the environment.
</P>
<P>
The first and the second such meetings were held in Athens in
July and December of 1997 and the third took place in the
southeastern Greek island of Rhodes in July 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
