<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russian Population May Decline by 8 Billion in 16 Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The Russian Statistics Agency
predicted that the population of Russia may shrink by eight
million people by the year 2016, the Interfax news agency reported
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Irina Sbarskaya, head of the agency's Demographics Department,
said that since the 1960s, the birth rate has been insufficient to
ensure the simple replenishment of the country's population.
</P>
<P>
To ensure replenishment, she said, every 100 women must have
215 children, not 124 as now.
</P>
<P>
She said the population of Russia has decreased by 2 million
people over the past seven years.
</P>
<P>
According to her agency, the population of Russia dropped by
0.28 percent, or 406,200, in the first half of this year to reach
145.9 million as of July 1.
</P>
<P>
As compared with the first half of the previous year, the rate
of population decline almost doubled. From January to June 1998,
the population of Russia diminished only by 226,700, or 0.15
percent.
</P>
<P>
The faster population decline was attributed to a rising death
rate as well as a decrease in migration from outside Russia.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
