<HEADLINE> Zambia Reaffirms "One-China" policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Zambian President Frederick
Chiluba Thursday reaffirmed "One-China" policy pursued by his
government while receiving credentials presented by new Chinese
Ambassador Peng Keyu.
</P>
<P>
He told the new ambassador here that Zambia appreciates and
supports " One-China" policy every single day."
</P>
<P>
Chiluba expressed his confidence that the Chinese people can
resolve their own problem.
</P>
<P>
He said that today the relations between Zambia and China is
warmest and very close.
</P>
<P>
"China is with us," he said, adding: China is "a friend of
Zambia and a friend of Africa." Chiluba said that Zambian
cherishes the friendship with China.
</P>
<P>
Zambia and China also have common views on international issues
 including environment protection and development, he said.
</P>
<P>
Chiluba highly spoke of the economic cooperation between the
two countries and thanked China for its assistance in various
fields like health care.
</P>
<P>
Chiluba said, "we will continue to work together to further
strengthen our relations." 
</P>
</TEXT>
