<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ibero-American Meeting of Ministers Begins </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, September 2 (Xinhua)-- Ibero-American Ministers of
Economy and Finance began Thursday in Havana a two-day meeting to
analyze repercussions of the world economic crisis on the region.
</P>
<P>
The conclusions of the meeting, which is taking place at Palace
of Conventions, will be presented at the 9th Ibero-American Summit
on November 15 and 16 in Havana.
</P>
<P>
Ibero-America here refers itself to all the Latin American
countries plus Spain and Portugal.
</P>
<P>
Participants at the second Ibero-American meeting of economy
and finance ministers will expose diverse national problems and
policies facing them, as well as an evaluation of results.
</P>
<P>
The 9th Ibero-American Summit will mainly discuss regional and
international financial situation in a globalized economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
