<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2000GMT, Thursday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak and Palestinian
National Authority Chairman Yasser Arafat will apparently sign a
revised Wye agreement in Alexandria, Egypt on Friday morning,
senior Israeli sources said.
</P>
<P>
The sources were quoted by Israel Radio as saying that
Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak, Jordan's King Abdullah and
United States Secretary of State Madeleine Albright will take part
in the signing ceremony. (BC-Israel-Palestine)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright arrived in
Alexandria, Egypt Thursday on the second leg of her regional tour
aimed at helping push the Mideast peace process forward.
</P>
<P>
Albright went straight into talks with Egyptian President Hosni
Mubarak after arriving in the Mediterranean port city to seek ways
to bridge the gap between the Palestinians and Israel over an
agreement on the implementation of the Wye peace accord signed
last October. (BC-Egypt-US-Albright)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright said on
Thursday that she is hopeful that the Palestinians and Israel will
soon reach an agreement on the implementation of the Wye peace
accord.
</P>
<P>
Albright made the remarks at a joint press conference with
Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr Moussa after her meeting with
President Hosni Mubarak in Egypt's Mediterranean port city of
Alexandria. (BC-Egypt-US-Mideast Peace)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- The Arab League (AL) on Thursday reiterated support
for the efforts to have economic sanctions on Iraq lifted.
</P>
<P>
The nine-year-old crippling international trade embargo on Iraq
should be lifted to ease the sufferings of the Iraqi people, AL
Assistant Secretary General Ahmad Bin Heli said.
</P>
<P>
The 22-nation pan-Arab forum rejects the continued attacks on
Iraqi sites by warplanes of the United States and Britain, Heli
told reporters after a meeting with Iraqi Permanent Delegate to
the Arab League Al-Sultan Al-Shawi. (BC-Arab League-Iraq) 
</P>
</TEXT>
