<HEADLINE> Annan Heads to Francophonie Summit in Canada </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 2 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General
Kofi Annan left here on Thursday afternoon for Canada to attend
the English Francophonie Summit, U.N. spokesman Fred Eckhard said.
</P>
<P>
Heads of State will begin arriving in Moncton, New Brunswick,
where the summit is to be held, he said.
</P>
<P>
Annan will be one of the speakers Friday, addressing
participants on the subject of youth, and his topic will be "Youth
and the Dialogue Among Civilizations," the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. chief will then return to New York on Friday
afternoon, he added. 
