<HEADLINE> Iraq Finishes Pumping Oil to Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Iraq on Thursday finished
pumping 10 million U.S. dollars worth of oil as assistance to
quake-hit Turkey, an Iraqi official said.
</P>
<P>
The unnamed official said in a statement carried by the Iraqi
News Agency that from last Sunday Iraq started pumping 100,000
barrels of oil per day to Turkey via the Iraqi-Turkish oil
pipelines to Turkey's Ceyhan harbor.
</P>
<P>
The official added that Iraq had finished pumping 500,000
barrels of oil so far to Turkey.
</P>
<P>
He said that a delegation from the Iraqi Red Crescent Society
left for Turkey earlier Thursday to coordinate with its Turkish
counterpart to draw up a distribution plan for the assistance to
victims of the earthquake.
</P>
<P>
The Iraqi Cabinet last Month decided to offer 10 million
U.S. dollars worth of oil as assistance to families of victims of
the earthquake.
</P>
<P>
Turkey was hit by an earthquake of 7.4 magnitude on August 17,
which left some 14,000 people killed and 43,000 others injured.
