<HEADLINE> Nigerian Senate Slashes 19 on the Ambassadorial </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABUJA, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The Nigerian senate Thursday
approved the recommendation of its foreign affairs committee
rejecting 19 of the 106 ambassadorial nominees submitted about
three weeks ago by President Olusegun Obasanjo.
</P>
<P>
Among those rejected by the 109-member upper house were 11 of
the 44 career ambassadors and 8 among the 62 political nominees.
</P>
<P>
Among the reasons given by the 12-member committee for the
rejection of some of the nominees was the need to reflect federal
character, a constitutional provision requiring the fair
representation of the country's 36 states and the federal capital
in appointments.
</P>
<P>
The senate also approved the recommendations of the committee
for the president to represent names for some of the states whose
nominees were rejected.
</P>
<P>
The nominations were engulfed controversy after it was
submitted by the president about three weeks ago, most of the
criticisms dwelling on the lopsidedness in favor of a few states.
</P>
<P>
Last week, the committee was forced to submit an interim report
 recommending that each state produces three nominees with the
federal capital producing one. 
</P>
</TEXT>
