<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Former Chilean leader Augusto
Pinochet was taken to hospital Thursday for a routine medical
check, police in charge of his house-arrest said.
</P>
<P>
Pinochet, who was arrested in a London hospital last October
while recovering from back surgery, had been taken to hospital for
checks a week ago.
</P>
<P>
He was arrested because a Spanish judge accused him of
responsibility for the deaths and disappearances of 3,000 people
and requested his extradition to Spain to face charges.
</P>
<P>
The Spanish judge wants to try him for the human rights abuses
alleged to be committed during his 1973-1990 rule in Chile.
</P>
<P>
Britain is scheduled to begin the extradition proceedings from
September 27.
</P>
<P>
On Pinochet's increasingly frequent visits to the doctor for
medical checks, he is accompanied by police.
</P>
<P>
The retired general's supporters said recently they fear the
83-year-old man is not well enough to face forthcoming court
hearings in Britain and possible trial in Spain.
</P>
<P>
His health problems are said to include depression as well as
diabetes and a weak heart. 
