Yeltsin had signed a presidential order concerning celebrations to
be held in Russia for the 50th anniversary of the People's
Republic of China. He expressed the wish that President Yeltsin's
forthcoming visit to China may further promote bilateral
relationship in a significant and constructive way.
</P>
<P>
Present at the meeting were He Luli, vice-chairwoman of the
Standing Committee of the National People's Congress, Chen
Junsheng, vice-chairman of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference, and Chen Haosu, vice-chairman of the Sino-
Russia Friendship Association.
</P>
<P>
Diplomatic envoys from some other Commonwealth of Independent
States countries to China were also present.
</P>
<P>
The Russian Branch of the WRSA was founded in 1989, and now has
more than 3,000 members, most of whom are scholars who had studied
or worked in the former Soviet Union. After returning to China,
they quickly became key figures in their fields.  
