<HEADLINE> Buckingham Palace Refuses to Comment on Diana Case </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The Buckingham Palace declined
to comment on Friday on the long-awaited French report on the car
crash that killed Princess Diana two years ago.
</P>
<P>
"There is no reaction from us," the Reuters quoted a spokesman
of the royal family as saying.
</P>
<P>
A spokeswoman for Diana's brother, Earl Spencer, who accused
the media of hounding her to death, is planning to make a
statement later on the French decision to drop manslaughter
charges against nine photographers and a motorcyclist in the 1997
crash.
</P>
<P>
The French lawyer for Harrods store owner Mohamed Al Fayed,
whose son Dodi was also killed in the crash, announced in Paris
that he would appeal the decision. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
