<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Down 1.32 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks decreased
189.25 points, or 1.41 percent, to close at 13,178.31 Friday.
</P>
<P>
Market turnover was 7.183 billion HK dollars (920 million U.S.
dollars), 305 million HK dollars (39 million U.S. dollars) more
than Thursday's turnover of 6.878 billion HK dollars (881 million
U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The Finance Counter, Utilities, Properties and Commerce and
Industry made across-the-board decreases of 1.33 percent, 1.86
percent, 1.42 percent and 1.05 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
China-related shares ended with the Hang Seng China Enterprises
Index up 0.84 percent while the Hang Seng China-Affiliated
Corporations Index went down 1.04 percent.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong stocks opened down 111.50 points, or 0.83 percent, at
13,255.50 Friday and closed the morning session at 13,101.03.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng Index opened 13,434.79 on Monday and it ended 13,
178.31 on Friday by losing 256.48 points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
