<HEADLINE> One Killed in Plane Crash in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 3 (Xinhua) -- At least one person was killed
when a five-seater Cesna 150 light plane crashed Thursday morning
in southern Philippines, a report of the Philippine News Agency
said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted Southern Command Chief Lt. General Edgardo
Espinosa as saying that no survivors were found at the crash site
at Piakan Bay in Zamboanga del Norte province in the southern
Philippines.
</P>
<P>
Espinosa said a floating body was recovered at the site, but
the cadavers remain unidentified for lack of identification papers
on them.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, the plane came from Dumaguete city in
Negros Oriental province, but the destination of the plane is
still unknown.
</P>
<P>
A team of divers from the Naval was dispatched to the area to
check the plane submerged in meters of sea water.
</P>
<P>
The search has been hampered by near zero visibility because of
intermittent rains in the area for the past two weeks, said the
report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
