<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rapid Increase of Breast Cancer Incidence in Asia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The incidence of breast
cancer in Asia, though lower than in Europe and America, is
apparently increasing rapidly, epidemiologists told an on-going
international cancer seminar in Tianjin today.
</P>
<P>
More than 400 specialists and scholars from 14 countries and
regions are attending the second Asian Seminar on Breast Cancer in
this port city in northeast China.
</P>
<P>
The specialists attribute the rise to the overall improvement
of living standards in Asia over recent years.
</P>
<P>
In China, the growth rate of such cancer in the ten major
cities has averaged 37 percent, according to the epidemiologist
with Shanghai experiencing the highest figures of 26.5 cases per
100,000 women, followed by Beijing and Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
Medical experts say that some 1.2 million women around the
world suffer from breast cancer, a common disease among women, and
500,000 of them will die from it every year. Growth rates around
the world vary between 5 to 20 percent.
</P>
<P>
Epidemiologists note that physical factors, biological
conditions, the environment, and intake of protein, may all
attribute to the increase. And they believe that a longer
menstrual period, first births over 35 years of age and short
breast feeding periods are the most probable causes.
</P>
<P>
Increased intakes of high fat, low fiber food, but little fruit
and vegetables in the daily diet may also lead to the disease.
</P>
<P>
They say that making more information about the disease widely
known, recommending a more practical diet, breast feeding, and a
healthier life style will play an important role in preventing and
controlling the disease.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990903.0114 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Missile Experts Refute Lee Teng-hui's Splittist Remarks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Chinese missile specialists
have pledged to speed up the development of missiles to enhance
China's national defense capabilities in a bid to maintain the
country's sovereignty and territorial integrity.
</P>
<P>
They said that they resolutely support the Chinese Communist
Party general secretary Jiang Zemin's eight-point proposal of
developing the cross-strait relations and promoting the process of
the peaceful reunification of the motherland.
</P>
<P>
These specialists expressed their pledge at a recent meeting
here to refute Lee Teng-hui's "two-state" splittist remarks.
</P>
<P>
Experts from the China Aerospace Machinery and Electronics
Corporation (CAMEC), a missile manufacturer, said that Lee Teng-
hui has underestimated the military strength of the Chinese People
's Liberation Army (PLA) and of the special position and capacity
of missiles in the national defense.
</P>
<P>
The CAMEC said it has developed several dozens of models of
missiles such as strategic, tactical, ground-to-ground, ground-to-
sea and ground-to-air missiles.
</P>
<P>
It said that it has made some breakthroughs in missile
manufacturing technology in accelerating the development and
manufacturing of a new generation of missiles.
</P>
<P>
China now boasts missiles of various altitudes, ranges and
speeds, it said, adding that they may strike at any targets with
precision.
</P>
<P>
They said Lee Teng-hui openly opposes the "one China" principle
and attempts to separate Taiwan from China, ignoring Taiwan
compatriots' desire for peace, stability, development, and
mutually beneficial cooperation and exchanges between both sides
of the Taiwan strait.
</P>
<P>
This, they pointed out, has seriously undermined the cross-
strait relations and basic interests of the compatriots on both
sides of the Taiwan strait, resulting in a tense situation across
the strait.
</P>
<P>
The world has but one China and Taiwan is an inalienable part
of China and the Chinese sovereignty and territorial integrity
brook no separation, they pointed out.
</P>
<P>
They stressed that the Taiwan issue cannot be delayed
indefinitely and the Chinese people will never allow Lee Teng-hui
to realize his evil plot. 
</P>
</TEXT>
