<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Number of China's Private Firms Hits Record High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The number of private
enterprises in China had reached 1.28 million by June this year,
80,000 more than at end of last year, the State Administration for
Industry and Commerce said today.
</P>
<P>
The number of people working in the sector hit 17.84 million,
up 22.4 percent from the corresponding period last year, and total
registered capital amounted to 817.7 billion yuan, up 24.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
During the January-June period, the economic returns of these
private firms improved remarkably. They registered an industrial
value of 370.5 billion yuan, a sales income of 350.5 billion yuan
and an export revenue of 1.5 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
An official with the administration pointed out that the rapid
growth of Chinese private firms helped alleviate the pressure on
the country's current employment problems and helped 720,000
workless find new jobs in the six months under review.
</P>
<P>
The number of limited companies increased by a big margin
during the same period, and now accounts for more than 50 percent
of all private enterprises.
</P>
<P>
He attributed this positive change mainly to the successful
switch by a number of state-owned enterprises to the private
sector, with company operators gradually introducing modern
techniques to streamline management.  
</P>
</TEXT>
