<HEADLINE> Int'l Symposium on Trade Unions Cooperation Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 3 (Xinhua) -- A week-long international
symposium on the work of trade unions in the period of transition
to the market economy opened here today.
</P>
<P>
The symposium is co-sponsored by the All-China Federation of
Trade Unions (ACFTU) and a visiting delegation from the General
Confederation of Trade Unions (GCTU) which consists of some member
countries of the Commonwealth of Independent States (CIS).
</P>
<P>
It aims at probing ways to safeguard the rights and interests
of the workers and to increase mutual understanding and trade
union cooperation between China and CIS countries.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Junjiu, vice president and first secretary of the
Secretariat of the ACFTU, said at the opening ceremony that the
celebrations to mark the 50th anniversary of the founding of the
People's Republic of China and the return of Macao are imminent,
and so this trade unions gathering is significant.
</P>
<P>
He said that although China and the CIS countries have
different domestic situations, their trade unions face similar
problems.
</P>
<P>
He said that "the Chinese trade unions hope to strengthen their
cooperation with all the trade unions of the world, including
those of the CIS countries, so as to contribute to the
establishment of a new international trade unions order".
</P>
<P>
Scherbakov Vladimir, head of the GCTU delegation, said that
even though there is a border between China and the CIS countries,
their existing traditional friendship has further strengthened.
</P>
<P>
"The exchanges between the trade unions will further promote
such friendship and cooperation between China and the CIS
countries," he added.
</P>
<P>
During the symposium, the representatives of the ACFTU will
brief the guests on the work of the Chinese trade unions, and the
CIS visitors will deliver speeches on their respective trade
unions and the current political and economic situation in their
countries.
</P>
<P>
The CIS visitors are here at the invitation of the ACFTU.
</P>
</TEXT>
