<HEADLINE> China Ready to Expand Cooperation With UNDP: Minister (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 3 (Xinhua) -- China is ready to continue and
expand its cooperation with the United Nations Development Program
(UNDP) in many areas, Minister of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation Shi Guangsheng said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Shi said in a speech at a seminar marking the 20th anniversary
of the cooperation between China and the UNDP that there are many
areas in which China can continue to cooperate with the UNDP.
</P>
<P>
China needs to go on raising the income of farmers and resolve
the problem of poverty in the rural areas. Out of its 1.2 billion
population, 900 million live in the countryside.
</P>
<P>
"China is striving to build a socialist market economy and a
country ruled by law. It is also carrying out more reforms and
trying to help improve the technical standards and management
style of small and medium-sized companies," said the minister.
</P>
<P>
"In addition, China needs to do a lot more in the development
of bilateral trade and economic cooperation with the developing
countries," he remarked.
</P>
<P>
"We hope that we can continue to keep and expand cooperation
with other countries and relevant international bodies like the
UNDP," added Shi.
</P>
<P>
He described the cooperation between China and the UNDP over
the past 20 years as "effective" and "fruitful." More than 840
cooperation projects have been successfully carried out in China,
with a total contribution of approximately 500 million US dollars
from the UNDP.
</P>
<P>
Those projects cover agriculture, industry, energy,
transportation, telecommunications, education, health care finance,
taxation, social security, poverty alleviation, the development of
women, economic structural reform and utilization of overseas
capital.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
