<DOCNO> XIE19990903.0143 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladesh's First Private EPZ to Be Developed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The development work of
Bangladesh's first private export processing zone (EPZ) on 68
hectares of land will begin in the second week of October this
year, the Independent daily newspaper reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
A large number of foreign investors from Singapore, United
States of America and Europe have expressed their keen interest in
the Rangunia Export Processing Zone (REPZ), which is located at
Rangunia, about 30 kilometers away from the country's southeastern
sea-port city of Chittagong, A. Qaiyum Chowdhury, managing
director of the Chittagong Industrial Park Limited, was quoted as
saying.
</P>
<P>
The REPZ would be divided into information technology valley
and agro-valley, and initially, a total of 100 industrial plots
including 20 for heavy industries would be developed over 42.4
hectares of land, Chowdhury said, adding that ultimately the
number of plots would increase to 250 and the area of the REPZ
would also be expanded to 280 hectares of land in phases.
</P>
<P>
Some 2.5 billion taka (about 50 million U.S. dollars) would be
spent for the infrastructural development of the REPZ, and with
implementation of the project, 25 billion taka (about 505 million
dollars) would be invested creating job opportunities for over
50,000 people, he disclosed.
</P>
<P>
The project would include a golf course, an artificial lake, a
recreational park, a greenbelt, an international standard hotel
and recreation center, and the project area would also be
surrounded by a ring road, he stated.
</P>
<P>
Besides, one 100-megawatt capacity generator would be installed
in the project site and one jetty and container terminal would
also be set up in the REPZ site, he said, hoping that the
operation of the zone would begin in 2000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
