<HEADLINE> India Factsheet (4): Head of State </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 3 (Xinhua) --
</P>
<P>
The president is head of state and commander-in-chief of the
armed forces.
</P>
<P>
The president is directly elected by an electoral college
consisting of elected members of both houses of parliament and the
legislative assemblies of the states. His term of office is 5
years and is eligible for re-election. He may be impeached for
violation of the Constitution.
</P>
<P>
The vice-president is the ex-officio chairman of the Rajya
Sabha and is elected by members of an electoral college consisting
of members of both houses of parliament.
</P>
<P>
The president exercises executive power on the advice of the
Council of Ministers, which is responsible to parliament. The
president appoints the prime minister and on the latter's
recommendation other ministers. Presidents in history:
</P>
<P>
Rajendra Prasad  (January 1950-May 1962)
</P>
<P>
Sarvepalli Radhakrishnan  (May 1962-May 1967)
</P>
<P>
Zakir Husain  (May 1967-May 1969)
</P>
<P>
Varahagiri Venkatagiri (May 1969-July 1969, Acting)
</P>
<P>
M. Hidayatullah  (July 1969-August 1969, Acting)
</P>
<P>
Varahagiri Venkatagiri (August 1969-August 1974)
</P>
<P>
Fakhruddin Ali Ahmed  (August 1974-February 1977)
</P>
<P>
B.D. Jatti  (February 1977-July 1977, Acting)
</P>
<P>
Neelam Sanjiva Reddy (July 1977-July 1982)
</P>
<P>
Giani Zail Singh  (July 1982-July 1987)
</P>
<P>
R. Venkataraman  (July 1987-July 1992)
</P>
<P>
Shanker Dayal Sharma  (July 1992-July 1997)
</P>
<P>
Kocheril Raman Narayanan  (July 1997-till date)
</P>
