<HEADLINE> Cross-Straits News Exchange Symposium </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, September 3 (Xinhua) -- A senior Chinese official has
said that academic exchanges between the Chinese mainland and
Taiwan region will not be affected by any interference, and that
nothing can hinder the process of the reunification of China.
</P>
<P>
Shao Huaze, president of the All-China Journalists Association,
made the remark at the ongoing 5th Symposium on News Exchange
between the Chinese mainland and Taiwan, Hong Kong, and Macao
regions which opened Thursday in Kunming, capital of southwest
China's Yunnan Province.
</P>
<P>
The three-day symposium, which was initiated in 1993, has
played a significant role in promoting mutual understanding and
friendship between journalists in the Chinese mainland and those
in Taiwan, Hong Kong, and Macao regions, Shao noted.
</P>
<P>
The symposium is being attended by nearly 70 representatives
from the Chinese mainland, and Taiwan, Hong Kong, and Macao
regions.  
</P>
</TEXT>
