<HEADLINE> Mexico Links Diplomacy to National Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Mexican Foreign Secretary
Rosario Green said Thursday that Mexico will widen ties with all
countries to contribute to national development.
</P>
<P>
Speaking on the diplomatic strategy before the Senate, Green
said the country should keep on upholding a principled "
independent and committed" policy.
</P>
<P>
Mexico has decided to take advantage of its geographical
location to link with more dynamic poles of the world economy, she
pointed out.
</P>
<P>
Mexico will become the only country having agreements of free
trade with the two most important economic blocs in the world,
referring to the treaty it already holds with the United States
and Canada, and another to be signed with the European Union at
the year end, she said.
</P>
<P>
Regarding Latin America, she said that relations between Mexico
and this region saw an "important change when communication and
direct dialogue strengthened" after President Ernest Zedillo met
many of his counterparts on the subcontinent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
