<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka's Regional Industrial Sector Being Developed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan government has
spent 3.12 million U.S. dollars on infrastructure development of
the regional industrial sector to reduce unemployment at regional
level, media sources said.
</P>
<P>
So far 5, 000 direct employment opportunities have been
provided in 32 industries which are operating in 14 industrial
parks in different parts of the country.
</P>
<P>
Once these establishments are in full operation, they will
generate 20,000 direct employment opportunities, Northwestern
Provincial Minister of Health and Cooperatives Jayaratne Herath
was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The minister spoke at Wednesday's seminar for local
industrialists.
</P>
<P>
The seminar was in connection with plans to establish a
multi-purpose industrial city on a 55 acre block of land in the
province.
</P>
<P>
The minister called for support from local industrialists to
extend their cooperation for the success of the project, the
sources said.
</P>
<P>
They added that the current government's industrial policy was
based on a multi-pronged strategy which features the promotion of
export-oriented industries and the provision of a comprehensive
network of infrastructure facilities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
