<HEADLINE> Cuban Parliament Leader Meets With U.S. Senators </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, September 2 (Xinhua)-- President of Cuba's National
Assembly Ricardo Alarcon met with three visiting U.S. senators on
Thursday and discussed with them the current relations between the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
Cuba and the United States have no diplomatic ties for nearly
four decades. They have only maintained a migratory accord since
May 1995.
</P>
<P>
Democratic Senators Tom Lampson, Danny Davis and Sanford Bishop
also met Cuban delegates from working commissions responsible for
agriculture, public health, international relations and judicial
affairs, the local press reported.
</P>
<P>
Bishop arrived here Wednesday while Danny Davis from Illinois
and Tom Lampson from Texas arrived here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Cuban authorities have said that the U.S. sanctions starting
1962 have caused Cuba 60 billion U.S. dollars in economic loss.
</P>
