<HEADLINE> Keane and Irwin out of Irish Euro Qualifiers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Ireland and Manchester United
skipper Roy Keane has been forced out of his country's next two
Euro 2000 qualifiers against Croatia and Malta after aggravation
of injuries.
</P>
<P>
Keane's United teammate Denis Irwin has also been ruled out of
the games by injury against Croatia on September 4 and Malta on
September 8.
</P>
<P>
Both players, aggravated injuries in the second half of Ireland
's 2-1 defeat of Yugoslavia on Wednesday night in Dublin, came off
before the end of the game.
</P>
<P>
Irwin was replaced in defense by Tottenham Hotspur's Stephen
Carr after 66 minutes and Keane in midfield by Blackburn's Lee
Carsley three minutes later.
</P>
<P>
Irish media reported that Keane, who injured his hamstring,
could also miss Manchester United's opening Champions League match
against Croatia Zagreb.
</P>
<P>
Irwin suffered a recurring injury to his Achilles tendon.
</P>
<P>
Ireland manager Mick McCarthy called up Stoke's Graham Kavanagh
and Ipswich's Matt Holland to his squad. 
