<HEADLINE> Rangers Cleared over Old Firm Clashes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The Scottish Premier League
investigation into last May's Old Firm fracas has cleared Rangers
of any breach of rules.
</P>
<P>
The central charge against the Ibrox club related to their
players' post-match celebrations, which angered watching Celtic
fans.
</P>
<P>
Rangers clinched the title with victory in the match at
Parkhead on May 2 - and then appeared to mock Celtic's traditional
huddle" celebrations at the end of the game.
</P>
<P>
But a commission dismissed allegations of any impropriety.
</P>
<P>
Celtic have already been fined 45,000 pounds by a separate
commission for their part in the infamous scenes, which included
referee Hugh Dallas being struck by a coin and three players red-
carded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
