<HEADLINE> Anti-Drug Agreement Finalized in Ottawa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The Organization of American
States (OAS) has finalized an unprecedented anti-drug agreement at
the end of a three-day meeting in Ottawa Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Under the Multilateral Evaluation Mechanism (MEM), all 34 OAS
members will enjoy a common set of indicators in measurement of
drug problems and anti-drug efforts in their countries.
</P>
<P>
The agreement will better coordinate joint action against drug
supply and demand problems, with the first round of
intergovernmental evaluations expected in January 2000.
</P>
<P>
In a statement released Thursday, Canadian Foreign Minister
Lloyd Axworthy hailed the MEM agreement, saying "it will be a
powerful new tool" in the fight against the trade in and abuse of
illicit drugs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
