<HEADLINE> Uganda Signs OAU Anti-Terrorism Convention </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Uganda Thursday signed the
 Convention on the Prevention and Combating of Terrorism, thus
becoming the 33rd signatory to the document adopted by the
Organization of African Unity (OAU).
</P>
<P>
The signing ceremony was held in the office of OAU Secretary
General Salim Ahmed Salim here.
</P>
<P>
Salim praised Uganda for its initiative to sign the convention
since the fight against terrorism needs collective efforts by
member states. He urged those who have not done so to come forward
and sign it.
</P>
<P>
Uganda's ambassador to Ethiopia Alex Kamugish said he was
pleased to sign the convention while Uganda is preparing a law
against terrorists.
</P>
<P>
He assured the OAU chief that Uganda will work hard to speedily
ratify the convention, and work with other member states in its
implementation.
</P>
<P>
Angola also signed the anti-terrorism convention on August 26.
</P>
</TEXT>
