<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. African Wrestlers Aim high at All-Africa Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 2 (Xinhua) -- South African wrestlers
aim for at least 10 medals in the up-coming All-Africa Games.
</P>
<P>
South African coach Hennie Minnaar said he was confident that
the wrestlers will repeat their achievements at the previous
Africa Games and the recent All-Africa championships.
</P>
<P>
In 1997 in Harare, the wrestlers won two gold medals on the
final day of the Africa Games to put South Africa at the top of
the medal table.
</P>
<P>
However, Minnaar expected the standard of wrestling to be
exceptionally high because it is a qualifying tournament for the
Sydney Olympics. More than 130 wrestlers from 16 countries and
regions have entered for the competition.
</P>
<P>
"Nigeria will undoubtedly be our strongest opponents in the
Free Style division," says Minnaar, quoted by South African Press
Association.
</P>
<P>
"while Egypt and Tunisia are rated among the world's best in
the Greco-Roman style." added Minnaar. South Africans will also
for the first time see an international female competition and the
Algerians and Tunisians are expected to dominate.
</P>
<P>
The South African Freestyle team is highly experienced and all
the wrestlers have had recent international exposure. Bennie
Labuschagne(69kg) and Jannie du Toit (76kg) are firm favorites for
golds. Both are current Africa champions and ranked among the top
12 in the world.
</P>
<P>
Two veterans of the Atlanta Olympics, Tjaart du Plessis (63kg)
and Andrew Davidson (130kg) are staging a comeback and are
expected to win medals. Tjonkie van Rensburg (58kg) brings vast
experience and exceptional skills to the competition and should do
very well.
</P>
<P>
Shaun Williams (54kg) will return from America where he is
currently studying and excelling in the tough Collegiate-circuit.
As the youngest member of the team he carries the hope for another
gold for South Africa.
</P>
<P>
Both Gideon Malherbe (76kg) and Markus Dekker (97kg) have won
medals at Africa championships in the Greco-Roman style and they
are expected to repeat.
</P>
<P>
Two Under-20 wrestlers, Raynard Mouton (63kg) and Juan Nel (
69kg),will use the Games to gain valuable international experience.
</P>
<P>
Amongt the women, the country's medal hopes are pinned on
Yvonnika Kruger (56kg) and Madelyn Swanepoel (75kg). However,
attention will also be fixed on the very talented Simphiwe
Mpungose (46kg) who will get her first taste of international
competition.
</P>
<P>
The South African competition will come from Algeria,
Democratic Republic of the Congo, Nigeria, Egypt, Tunisia, Senegal,
Ivory Coast,Tanzania, Namibia, Cameroon, Kenya, Madagascar,
Mauritius, Central African and Chad. 
</P>
</TEXT>
