<HEADLINE> Austrian President to Visit Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Austrian President Thomas
Klestil is to pay a visit to Iran on September 20, the first by a
Western European head of state in 20 years.
</P>
<P>
Press reports here quoted Gerhard Rainer, director general of
Austrian Foreign Ministry's Cultural Department, as saying the
visit is aimed at boosting bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
"The two countries' officials will concentrate on exploring
ways of promoting bilateral cooperation and discussing joint
programs, and strengthen political, cultural and economic ties
between Iran and Austria," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Austrian official said the two nations "had good mutual
relations in the past, including in the holding of the conference
of dialog between Islam and Christianity." The second round of the
conference is expected in Vienna in September or October.
</P>
<P>
Tehran has normalized relations with European Union members
states, which were marred by Iran's condemnation of British
writer Salmon Rushdie for his book The Satanic Verses.
</P>
<P>
Rainer said the two sides will cooperate in language teaching,
archeological projects and academic undertaking, hold an
Iran-Austria Culture Week and an exhibition of Austrian
architecture, and promote tourism between them.
</P>
<P>
Expressing welcome to Iranian President Mohammad Khatami's
proposal for dialog among civilizations, Rainer said his country
believes "the best way to remove misunderstandings is through
dialog between peoples." 
</P>
</TEXT>
