<HEADLINE> Over 300,000 Armed Prospectors in Lunda-Sul, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, September (Xinhua) -- Angola denounced the existence of
over 300, 000 illegal and armed diamond searchers in the northeast
province of Lunda- Sul, the National Diamond Enterprise (Endiama)
said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Among those armed prospectors are citizens of Democratic
Republic of Congo, South Africa, Mali and Angola, including
Angolan rebels led by Jonas Savimbi, revealed the company in an
interview with the National Radio of Angola (RNA).
</P>
<P>
The illegal diamond prospectors in the areas with an abundance
of diamond deposits in the Lunda-Sul Province are currently
undertaking their prospecting for the mineral, said Endiama, the
national diamond monopolizing company.
</P>
<P>
Due to the excellent military equipment of the illegal diamond
searchers, the guards of the mines faced difficulties in the
fighting with them. Only a coordination between the management of
Endiama and the defense and security forces can clear up the
areas, said the source of Endiama.
</P>
<P>
Endiama vowed to take measures in the near future to crack
down on the rampant illegal prospecting activities in Lunda-Sul in
northeast Angola, which is an important diamond-producing country
in Africa.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the rebels of the National Union for Total
Independence of Angola (UNITA) also participated in the
circumscription, launching attacks and conducting prospecting,
earning millions of dollars which are used for aquisition of
military equipment supporting the war. 
</P>
</TEXT>
