<HEADLINE> Sino-Thai Relations Enjoy Sound, Steady Development: Jiang (Part 1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The relations between China
and Thailand have seen a "sound and steady" development despite
the vicissitudes of the international situation, visiting Chinese
President Jiang Zemin said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
At the welcoming state banquet hosted by Thai King Bhumibol
Adulyadej, Jiang said that since the establishment of diplomatic
ties 24 years ago, there have been frequent exchanges of visits by
the leaders of the two countries and people-to-people contacts.
</P>
<P>
"Areas for bilateral cooperation have expanded and more and
more common ground has been achieved between the two sides on
regional and international issues," said Jiang, who arrived here
Thursday afternoon for a state visit as the king's guest.
</P>
<P>
He mentioned the Joint Statement on the Plan of Action for the
21st Century signed by the two countries earlier this year, saying
it outlines the future framework and charts the direction for the
development of bilateral relations and cooperation in the new
century.
</P>
<P>
"We can say that China and Thailand have already established an
all-round partnership of good-neighborliness and mutual trust
which can be seen as an example of good-neighborly friendship and
mutually beneficial cooperation between countries with different
social systems," he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that to further consolidate and develop the friendly
relations and cooperation between China and Thailand not only
conforms to the fundamental interests of the two countries and the
common aspiration of the two peoples, but also conduces to peace,
stability and development in the region.
</P>
<P>
He reviewed the long lasting friendship between China and
Thailand, which can be traced back to as early as the first
century. More
nnnn
</P>
