<HEADLINE> China to Host 1999 World Habitat Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, September 2 (Xinhua) -- This year's World Habitat Day
with the theme of "Cities for All" will be held in Dalian, a
northern port city in China, on October 4, Acting Executive
Director Klaus Toepfer of the U.N. Centre for Human Settlements
(Habitat) announced here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Other activities in China include Sustainable Cities Program
(SCP) support to China's Wuhan city and disaster mitigation
measures following the Yangtze floods in 1998, Toepfer said at a
press briefing.
</P>
<P>
Also as part of the 1999 World Habitat Day celebrations, a
major conference will be held in Shenyang, the capital of
Liaoning Province in northeast China, starting on October 5, he
said, adding that the conference will be opened by himself.
</P>
<P>
He said China is an active partner in the global Sustainable
Cities Program (SCP), a joint program promoted by the Habitat and
the U.N. Environmental Program (UNEP) since 1996.
</P>
<P>
Toepfer explained that as a global program, the SCP provides
municipal authorities and their partners in the public, private
and community sectors with improved environment planning and
management capacities.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the SCP has promoted the exchange of knowledge
and expertise among cities, undertaking demonstration projects in
some 40 cities worldwide, saying these city demonstrations
involve environment management strategies, action plans and
priority technical cooperation and capital investment projects
for the cites concerned. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
