Mexican State of Chiapas, but caused no personal or material
damage.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter was situated along the Pasific coast of Chaiapas
State, 20 kilometers beneath the surface of the Earth.
</P>
<P>
A report from the Seismology Institute said the earthquake was
caused by movements of the tectonic plate. 
