<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Minister Tells French How Much Chinese </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Zhao said that 100 years later, the Chinese people are living a
totally different life and are fully confident to enter the new
millennium with other peoples of the world.
</P>
<P>
He said that 100 years ago, Chinese women entered a new century
with bound feet. Today, they entered the final match of the
Women's Soccer World Cup held last summer in the United States.
</P>
<P>
This dramatic change reflected not only the great changes of
the life of Chinese women in the past 100 years, but also the
great changes lived by the whole Chinese society, he said.
</P>
<P>
Zhao said that since China launched the policy of economic
reform and opening in 1978, the life style of the Chinese has been
undergoing fundamental transformations, which are reflected in
their changing culture of food, clothes, transport and housing.
</P>
<P>
With increasing incomes, more and more Chinese are capable of
making choice between Chinese food and Western food, including
French wine and cheese, and are traveling abroad, he said.
</P>
<P>
Western suits, jeans, sportswear, and feminine pret-a-porter
have already become commonalities for Chinese people, he said.
</P>
<P>
Zhao said that the Chinese people are becoming more choosy
about what they should buy. For instance, they are wondering
whether they should accept too much American culture like
Disneyland and Hollywood.
</P>
<P>
Chinese people are also more and more familiar with the role
and function of laws and legal rules in their life and are using
them to protect their personal interests, he said.
</P>
<P>
He gave "Qiu Ju Makes Suit Against Her Husband," a film
starring actress Gong Li, as an example of how an ordinary woman
in the Chinese countryside can take advantage of the protection of
law to seek a better life. 
</P>
</TEXT>
