<HEADLINE> Uruguay's Industry Production Falls </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Uruguay's industry
production shrank 6.5 percent in the second quarter of this year
compared to the same period in 1998, the National Institute of
Statistics said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The biggest fall was registered in textiles, clothing, leather
and non-metallic minerals, the institute said in a report.
</P>
<P>
Experts said the fall reflects the country's economic recession
after the Asian crisis and the devaluation of the Brazilian
currency, the real.
</P>
<P>
The textile sector slumped 25.7 percent, followed by non-
metallic minerals, metallic products, materials and equipment.
</P>
<P>
The production of basic metallic manufacturing grew 7.7 percent,
followed by chemical industry at 6.9 percent and food, drinks and
tobacco at 1.2 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
