<HEADLINE> Chile, Costa Rica Negotiate Trade Accord </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Costa Rica and Chile on
Thursday started negotiations on a protocol of tariff reductions,
sources from the Costa Rican Foreign Trade Ministry told Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
Trade between the two countries reached 49.1 million U.S.
dollars in 1998. Chile exported 29 million U.S. dollars worth of
products to Costa Rica, which in return exported 20 million
dollars to Chile.
</P>
<P>
Chile, Costa Rica, Nicaragua, Honduras, El Salvador and
Guatemala ended talks on parts of the standards of a free trade
treaty here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Due to their different levels of development, the norms of
access to free trade markets will be negotiated in a bilateral way.
Now Chile and Nicaragua have started talks with their partners and
hoped to conclude them before next month, the same deadline set by
Costa Rica.
</P>
<P>
The other three Central American countries have decided to
negotiate together with Chile. 
