<HEADLINE> IAAF to Clear Jayasinghe of Doping Charges: Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The world athletics ruling
body IAAF is set to clear Sri Lanka's 1997 world 200m runner-up
Susanthika Jayasinghe of doping charges, a press report said on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Jayasinghe's manager Tony Campbell was quoted as saying in the
English language The Island newspaper that the IAAF was expected
to exonerate her within a week.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted Campbell as saying that the IAAF had actually
cleared her of any wrongdoing in July but an announcement had been
delayed because the organization was involved in arranging the
world athletics championships in Seville, Spain.
</P>
<P>
"The IAAF secretary apologized to me and said that since they
had so many other work including organizing the world games he
could not attend to this matter," Campbell was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Jayasinghe, who tested positive for a banned steroid, was
suspended in April last year, but her ban was lifted four months
later after a local hearing. However, the IAAF was unhappy over
the inquiry and referred her case to an arbitration panel.
</P>
</TEXT>
