<HEADLINE> New Zealand Stocks Finish Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand sharemarket
closed lower here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 Index ended 15 points lower at 2,139 with a turnover
of 51 million NZ dollars (24.4 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Among the leading stocks, Baycorp Holdings and Auckland Airport
 edged up 2 cents each to 603 and 299 cents respectively.
</P>
<P>
Carter Holt Harvey fell 7 cents to 222 cents, Telecom five to
863 cents, Fletcher Paper 4 to 136 cents, Fletcher Forests 3 to 86
cents, Fletcher Energy 2 to 494 cents, and both Brierley
Investments and Guiness Peat Group lost 1 cent to 44 and 155 cents
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Fletcher Building closed unchanged at 268 cents. 
</P>
