<HEADLINE> Beijing Greeting National Day with Cinematic Works </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Two films "National Anthem"
and "Spring Rhapsody" will appear in Beijing's cinemas on
September 9, describing the experiences of China's two well-known
musicians, Nie Er and Shi Guangnan, the former of whom composed
the national anthem.
</P>
<P>
A series of other films and television and radio plays will
also be released soon as part of the activities to celebrate the
50th anniversary of the People's Republic of China on October 1.
</P>
