<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-President Meets With Uruguayan Defense Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-President Hu
Jintao met with visiting Uruguayan Minister of National Defense
Juan Luis Storace and his party here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
"Sino-Uruguayan relationships have developed smoothly since the
two countries forged diplomatic ties, with an increasing high
level exchange of visits growing along with cooperation in various
fields," said Hu.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his appreciation to Uruguay for its adherence to
the "One-China" policy, and said China attaches importance to
developing friendship and cooperative ties with Uruguay and hopes
that both sides work together to further promote the military ties
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Speaking of the Taiwan issue, Hu noted that the essence of the
"two-states" remarks by Lee Teng-hui is to negate the principle of
"One China" and to separate Taiwan from China, which will
certainly be firmly opposed and strongly condemned by the Chinese
government and all Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
"It is the common aspiration of the entire Chinese nation to
develop the relationship across the Taiwan Strait and to advance
the country's reunification cause," said Hu. Anyone attempting to
obstruct this historical trend will do so in vain.
</P>
<P>
Storace reiterated that Uruguay will unswervingly keep to the "
One-China" policy, and it will, as always, support China's
peaceful reunification cause. "Uruguay will continue to enhance
its friendship and cooperative relations with China," he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
