<HEADLINE> Kenyan President Urges to Shun Food Imports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan President Daniel arap
Moi has said that it is absurd for Kenyans to import foodstuff
which could be produced in abundance locally.
</P>
<P>
The president made the remarks Thursday when opening the
Mombasa Show sponsored by the Agricultural Society of Kenya in
Coast Province in east Kenya, local media reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
Moi noted that it was ridiculous for the country to import farm
produces such as eggs which local poultry farmers can easily
produce, and called on relevant government departments to rectify
this anomaly for the benefits of local farmers.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that Kenya are importing such farm produces as
eggs and fruits from South Africa.
</P>
<P>
The president reiterated that the agriculture sector remained
to be the backbone of the country's economic growth, which not
only provides food requirements but also creates employment for
the majority of rural folks.
</P>
<P>
He observed that the country would continue to experience high
food demand throughout the next century due to rapid population
growth.
</P>
<P>
He urged agricultural and livestock officials to advise farmers
on which crop to grow and which animals to keep, taking advantage
of the soil and climate conditions of the farmers' localities.
</P>
<P>
Sound management and appropriate farming methods will bring the
 potential into full play for substantial growth in the
agriculture sector, the president added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
