<HEADLINE> HKSAR, Ecuador Sign Visa Abolition Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HKSAR) of China and the Republic of Ecuador
signed a visa abolition agreement here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
"The agreement gives visa-free access for a period up to 90
days to HKSAR passport holders visiting Ecuador, " a HKSAR
government spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
According to the spokesman, the agreement will take effect on
October 3, 1999. Nationals of Ecuador will likewise enjoy 90 days'
visa-free access to Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said: "We welcome the Agreement, which signifies
the confidence of the government of Ecuador in Hong Kong and the
HKSAR passport."
</P>
<P>
Ecuador is the 61st country (territory) granting visa-free
access to HKSAR passport holders. 
</P>
