<HEADLINE> UPU Elects Heads of International Bureau </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Thomas Leavey from the United
States was re-elected as director general of the International
Bureau (IB) of the Universal Postal Union (UPU) at the ongoing
22nd Universal Postal Congress (UPC) here today.
</P>
<P>
He will serve another five-year term till the convocation of
the next UPC.
</P>
<P>
Moussibahou Mazou from Congo (Brazzaville) was also re-elected
for another five-year term as deputy director general of the IB of
the UPU, beating another candidate R.U.S. Prasad from India.
</P>
<P>
Leavey said after his re-election at the congress that he will
lead the 189 member countries of the UPU to push forward the
reform of postal services and face the challenges of the 21st
century.
</P>
<P>
He said that he will place importance on letting the developing
countries integrate in the worldwide postal network. He pledged to
pay equal attention to every member of the UPU regardless of their
size and region.  
</P>
