<HEADLINE> Ballot Result in E. Timor may be Announced on Saturday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian Defense
Minister/Armed Forces Chief Gen. Wiranto hinted here Friday that
the result of the August 30 autonomy ballot in East Timor could be
made public on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
"Foreign Minister Ali Alatas informed me of the announcement
schedule through phone talks," Wiranto told newsmen at the
Parliament Building.
</P>
<P>
He said the military is preparing two battalions of troops to
safeguard the announcement.
</P>
<P>
The two battalions of troops aboard Air Force airplanes will
depart for East Timor to reinforce the police contingent assigned
to safeguard the ballot announcement, he added.
</P>
<P>
According the United Nations Mission in East Timor (UNAMET)
which organized the ballot, more than 98 percent of the total
450,000 registered voters cast their votes during the polling day
in or outside East Timor.
</P>
<P>
The direct ballot will decide whether East Timor will enjoy a
wide-ranging autonomy under Indonesia or get independence.
</P>
<P>
East Timor, a former Portuguese colony, integrated into
Indonesia in 1976, but the move has never been recognized by the
United Nations.
</P>
<P>
In January this year, the Indonesian government proposed to
give wide-ranging autonomy to East Timor. In May, the U.N.,
Indonesia and Portugal decided to hold a direct ballot for the
future of the territory. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
