<DOCNO> XIE19990903.0461 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets Thai Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese President
Jiang Zemin said here Friday that the all-round healthy and steady
partnership of good neighborliness and friendly cooperation
already established between China and Thailand surely embraces
broad prospects for development.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with Thai Prime Minister Chuan Leekpai Friday
morning, Jiang said such a partnership conforms to the fundamental
interests and aspirations of China and Thailand and the two
peoples.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said Thailand is one of China's closest partners of
cooperation in the region. He said the two countries treat each
other with sincerity and trust each other since they established
diplomatic relations 24 years ago and have thus enjoyed fruitful
cooperation in politics, economy, culture and science and
technology.
</P>
<P>
He said economic and trade cooperation between China and
Thailand has continued to maintain a good momentum of development
under joint efforts, with a sustained increase in bilateral trade
volume and a number of large cooperation projects under
negotiation.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese president expressed his confidence that bilateral
economic and trade cooperation will gain further development.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said he is pleased to see that the efforts made by the
Thai government and people to overcome the difficulties brought by
the Asian financial crisis, which broke out two years ago, have
born remarkable success, as a good momentum of economic recovery
has emerged in Thailand.
</P>
<P>
He said there is no difficulty which cannot be overcome so long
as the peoples of various countries unite and fight against it
indomitably.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting, Chuan Leekpai said this visit by President
Jiang, which came when the Chinese people are about to celebrate
the 50th anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of
China and the Thai people are holding nationwide celebrations for
the 72nd birthday of King Bhumibol Adulyadej, constitutes a major
happy event in his country.
</P>
<P>
The Thai prime minister said the joint statement issued by
China and Thailand on a Plan of Action for the 21st century will
give great impetus to the development of the relations between the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
He said the development of economic and trade ties between
Thailand and China is beneficial to the development of both
countries.
</P>
<P>
Chuan Leekpai expressed his gratitude to China for its selfless
assistance to Thailand during the Asian financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
He said the correct and firm stand and policies adopted by
China have provided the best support for countries swept by the
crisis.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese president arrived in Thailand on September 2.
</P>
</TEXT>
