<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Most Chinese Cities Report Good Air Quality </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Most Chinese cities reported
stable air quality this week, according to a report released today
by the China Environment Monitoring Center.
</P>
<P>
From August 27 to September 2, nine cities including Kunming,
Suzhou, Fuzhou, Nanning, Ningbo, Guilin, Zhanjiang, Xiamen and
Haikou enjoyed excellent air quality.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai, Zhengzhou, Tianjin, Wuhan, Xi'an, Shijiazhuang, Jinan
and 20 other cities reported good air quality during the week,
according to the report.
</P>
<P>
However, Hohhot suffered from moderate pollution of suspended
particles, and Urumqi, Lanzhou, Guangzhou, Taiyuan, Xining,
Beijing, Yinchuan and Chongqing reported slight air pollution.
</P>
<P>
The major problem in Guangzhou, Beijing, Shanghai and Wuhan was
nitrogen oxide, while in Chongqing and Guiyang sulfur dioxide was
the main pollutant, with most of other cities suffering from
suspended particles.  
</P>
</TEXT>
