<HEADLINE> Chinese Enterprise Permitted to Expand lumbering Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Foreign Trade
and Economic Cooperation has recently given permission to the
Harbin International Economic and Technological Cooperation Corp.
in northeast China's Heilongjiang Province to expand lumbering
business in Russia.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese enterprise will soon travel to Khabarovsk in Russia
's far east to undertake a project which involves felling three
million cubic meters of timber.
</P>
<P>
Deputy General Manager Yang Qiusheng said today that the
project is under the direct management of his company, and the
total investment is estimated at 50 million yuan (about six
million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Yang said that a large part of the labor force and equipment
will be hired, bought or rented in Russia, and all the cut timber
will be transported back to China for sale.
</P>
<P>
According to him, Russia's forestry authorities are supporting
the project, as it reduces the possibility of an infection of tree
insects following disastrous forest fires last year.
</P>
<P>
"The company is the first to get permission for such work since
regulations were introduced on strengthening the administration of
Sino-Russian exploitation and utility of forest resources on April
26," said Yang.
</P>
<P>
Chinese officials said that the premiers of the two states
signed a contract concerning timber imports and exports during
their fourth meeting last February.  
</P>
</TEXT>
