<DOCNO> XIE19990903.0477 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Feature: Controversy over Interest Tax Makes Chinese Feel More Like Tax Payers (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
When the chain store "Makro", which originated in the
Netherlands, opened its branches in Beijing, it printed the
consumer taxes a customer has to pay on the receipts. However,
never having heard of such practice, one customer reportedly said
to a sales manager, "I never pay tax in other stores, so why do I
have to pay it here?"
</P>
<P>
But today, everyone knows that other stores also are obliged to
include taxes in their prices but don't highlight the fact.
</P>
<P>
Liu said that the government is beefing up efforts to collect
personal income tax, and as a result, people in Beijing have found
in recent months that a new item was added to their salary sheet:
the amount deducted for personal income tax. All these changes
have contributed to the new tax awareness of the general public.
</P>
<P>
Wang Jiafu, a civil law expert and senior Chinese legislator,
said that when talking about the "tax-payer mentality", the
government and the media used to blame tax evaders but never
mention the responsibility of the government to serve the people.
</P>
<P>
This situation has now changed too.
</P>
<P>
According to reports, nine officials representing 2.81 million
tax payers in Nanning, capital of south China's Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region, including its mayor Lin Guoqiang, last year
publicly received their monthly salary to demonstrate that they
are accountable to the people.
</P>
<P>
The leading official newspaper People's Daily also published a
commentary recently to criticize officials who take advantage of
the people.
</P>
<P>
"Those (officials) who take the gratitude of the public for
granted or even make unreasonable demands of them should be
punished," it said.
</P>
<P>
The complaining woman in the police station later said in an
interview, "If all the people in society, including government
officials, have the 'tax payer mentality', it's worth paying our
due taxes." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
