<HEADLINE> Ugly Brawl Stains Asian Basketball Championship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUKUOKA, Japan, September 3 (Xinhua) -- An out-of-tempered
fight to the end of the game between Bahrain and Philippines
stained the so-far clean Asian Basketball Championship on Friday
at the Fukuoka International Center.
</P>
<P>
Bahrain's Malalla Ahmad chased after Sese Jovito of Philippines
for about half of the court before Jovito was knocked down when
the 11-12 placing playoff game had 1:20 to go.
</P>
<P>
The brawl soon turned into a full-court fight involving almost
all the players of Bahrain and half of the Philippines, with some
players even picking up court-side chairs to hit their rivals.
</P>
<P>
The game resumed five minutes later before Malalla and Jovito
both were dispelled.
</P>
<P>
Both teams just stood as the time was running out in the rest
of the game, which was taken by Philippines, 83-75.
</P>
<P>
Punishments for the two players will come out after the game
report is handed in to the technical commission of the Asian
Basketball Association.
</P>
<P>
In Friday's other placing games, Uzbekistan finished ninth
after beating the United Arab Emirates 70-56 while Hong Kong of
China defeated Thailand 68-53 to take the 13th place.
</P>
<P>
China will meet Chinese Taipei and defending champion South
Korea is to face Saudi Arab in Saturday's semi-finals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
