<HEADLINE> Australian Share market Slips 1 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The Australian stock market
shed more than one percent Friday with banking stocks among the
biggest losers.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark all ordinaries index slipped 31.3 points to
2,962.4.
</P>
<P>
Local experts said investors took their negative cue from Wall
Street, where ongoing interest rate fears pushed the Dow Jones
Industrial Average index down 94.67 to 10,843.21 points.
</P>
<P>
On the local bourse, the all industrials index off-loaded 56.6
points to 5,100.2, while the all resources index shed 10.7 points
to 1,299.2.
</P>
<P>
The banking index tumbled 102.8 to 6251.0 points, dragged back
by National Australia bank slumping 58 to 15.24 U.S. dollars and
the Commonwealth Bank shedding 39 to 15.71 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
National turnover was 360.19 million stocks traded for 547.48
million U.S. dollars. Falling stocks outnumbered rising stocks 716
to 420 and 457 stocks remained steady. 
