<HEADLINE> Contraband Gold Seized In Mumbai Airport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Indian Airport customs and
air intelligence unit in Mumbai, 1,400 km southwest of here,
seized 21 kilograms of gold Friday.
</P>
<P>
The gold, worth about 200,000 U.S. dollars, was found from an
air India flight from Dubai via Abu Dhabi, the Press Trust of
India (PTI) reported.
</P>
<P>
The gold bars bearing Swiss markings were wrapped in four
packets and concealed in the roof of the rear toilet, PTI quoted
customs officials as saying.
</P>
