<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Lower on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
SINGAPORE, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Share prices closed lower
on Singapore Stock Market Friday following Wall Street's overnight
decline amid dominant U.S. interest rate concerns.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) lost 25.03 points to
end at 2,093.18 points.
</P>
<P>
The total turnover stood at 228.09 million shares valued at
421.35 million Singapore dollars (250.59 million U.S. dollars).
Losers led gainers by 226 to 80 with 141 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Sunway topped the volume chart with a turnover of 25.85
million units. It was followed by Gen Int that had 22.41 million
shares done. AFP ranked the third with 16.69 million counters
changing hands.
</P>
<P>
SPH led gainers of the day going up 50 cents to finish at
28.50 Singapore dollars. Venture picked up 40 cents to close at
15.90 Singapore dollars. PacCent edged up 30 cents to end at 8.30
Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, C&AMP;C was the biggest loser of the day as it
dropped 1.65 Singapore dollars to close at 7.45 Singapore dollars.
Ge Life was down 50 cents to finish at 19.20 Singapore dollars .
Creative shed 30 cents to end at 16.70 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that besides the negative effect from the Wall
Street, the sharp decline of index-linked Cycle &AMP; Carriage, which
slumped 18 percent after it said its sole distribution rights to
Mercedes-Benz cars are under review, also dampened sentiment.
</P>
</TEXT>
