<HEADLINE> PLA Chief of General Staff Meets Uruguayan Guests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Fu Quanyou, chief of the
General Staff of the Chinese People's Liberation Army (PLA), met
here today with visiting Uruguayan Defense Minister Juan Luis
Storace and expressed his pleasure over the positive development
of ties between the two countries and their armed forces.
</P>
<P>
Fu, also a member of the Central Military Commission, said he
is eager to further the cooperation between the two armies.
</P>
<P>
Fu briefed Storace and his party on China's domestic situation
and refuted Lee Teng-hui's "Two States" theory, saying that Lee
Teng-hui openly issued separatist remarks, denied the "One China"
principle, and attempted to separate Taiwan from China.
</P>
<P>
"It is absolutely unacceptable for the Chinese people," he said,
noting that the PLA bears the responsibility for safeguarding
national sovereignty and territorial integrity, and they will foil
any conspiracy to split the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Storace expressed his willingness to promote the friendly
cooperation between the two countries and armies. He respects
China's stance on the Taiwan issue, and said that Uruguay will
continue to adhere to the "one China" position.  
</P>
