<HEADLINE> China Happy with UNDP Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Chinese State Councilor Wu Yi
today said that China is satisfied with the cooperation it has
enjoyed with the United Nations Development Program (UNDP) in the
past 20 years.
</P>
<P>
"The extensive and fruitful cooperation between China and the
UNDP has helped China introduce advanced foreign technologies and
resolve many problems in the process of economic construction,"
said Wu, when meeting with UNDP Assistant Administrator Nay Htun
and other foreign participants at a symposium here marking the two
decades of working together.
</P>
<P>
"Although China has made great achievements in economic
development," Wu said, "the country is still faced with lots of
problems demanding prompt solutions."
</P>
<P>
"The country hopes to expand cooperation with the UNDP and
other international organizations," Wu added.
</P>
<P>
Nay Htun, also director of UNDP Regional Bureau for Asia and
the Pacific, expressed his gratitude to Wu for her comments. He
said that the UNDP will make further contributions to China's
reform and opening as well as its modernization plans.  
</P>
