<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets Thai National Assembly President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese President
Jiang Zemin expressed hope Friday that the National People's
Congress of China and the National Assembly of Thailand will
continue to strengthen exchanges and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with Thai National Assembly President Wan
Muhammad Nor Matha, Jiang said the National People's Congress of
China and the National Assembly of Thailand have always maintained
close exchanges.
</P>
<P>
The visit to China by Wan Muhammad Nor Matha last year and the
visit to Thailand by Chairman of the Standing Committee of the
National People's Congress of China Li Peng earlier this year,
among other exchanges, have deepened the mutual understanding and
cooperation between the parliaments of the two countries, Jiang
said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said China and Thailand are good neighbors, partners and
friends, with relations dating back more than 2,000 years. The two
countries now enjoy close cooperation in the fields of politics,
economy and culture, he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang expressed his satisfaction over the development of Sino-
Thai relations and his confidence in the prospects of further
development of cooperation in the future, saying there are no
historical problems, nor any current conflict of interests between
the two countries.
</P>
<P>
On the Asian financial crisis, Jiang said the Thai government
and people, after more than two years of arduous efforts, have
weathered the most difficult time since the outbreak of the crisis,
and the Thai economy is now moving steadily toward recovery.
</P>
<P>
He said that during the crisis, the Chinese government held to
its promise not to devalue the renminbi, the Chinese currency, and
tried to aid Thailand and other countries severely struck by the
crisis, despite the great difficulties inflicted by the crisis
upon China.
</P>
<P>
The Thai National Assembly president said Thailand and China
have been enjoying a long-term close cooperation. The current
visit to Thailand by President Jiang constitutes a major event in
the history of the relations between the two countries and will
definitely have an important and profound impact on the
development of such relations, he added.
</P>
<P>
He said the Thai National Assembly and the National People's
Congress of China have maintained close exchanges between them,
adding that his visit to China last year and the visit to Thailand
by Chairman of the Standing Committee of the National People's
Congress of China Li Peng, among other exchanges, have promoted
the friendship between the peoples of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He said the Thai National Assembly will further strengthen its
exchanges with the Chinese National People's Congress in the
future.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Chinese President Jiang Zemin also met former Thai
Prime Minister Chavalit Yongchaiyudh this morning. Jiang thanked
Chavalit for his constructive work to accelerate the development
of Sino-Thai friendship and cooperation over the past years.
</P>
</TEXT>
