<HEADLINE> Australia' World War I Veteran Dies at 101 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 3 (Xinhua) -- One of Australia's last World
War I veterans, Howard Pope, died Friday at the age of 101, seven
weeks before his 102nd birthday.
</P>
<P>
AAP reported that Pope died in his sleep at the Daw Park
Repatriation and General Hospital in Adelaide Friday morning after
a short illness.
</P>
<P>
After enlisting in 1916, Pope served on the Western Front as a
machine-gunner in the 27th Battalion. He took part in every action
involving the battalion and returned to Australia in July 1919.
</P>
<P>
He returned to France last year to receive the French Legion of
Honor medal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
