<HEADLINE> HK, Sri Lanka Sign Accord on Fugitive Offenders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HKSAR) and Sri Lanka signed an agreement
Friday for the surrender of fugitive offenders.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed by Hong Kong Secretary for Security
Regina Ip and Sri Lankan Ambassador to China R C A Vandergert.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the signing ceremony, Ip said, "The signing of the
agreement signifies the joint commitment of both Sri Lanka and the
HKSAR in fighting international crime and our close cooperation in
matters of criminal justice and international law enforcement.
</P>
<P>
"More importantly, it also demonstrates the continuity of the
rule of law in the HKSAR," she noted.
</P>
<P>
The Agreement for the Surrender of Fugitive Offenders with Sri
Lanka is the 12th of its kind concluded by Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
It sets out the conditions for the surrender of fugitive
offenders between the two places and contains the usual safeguards
found in similar international agreements.
</P>
<P>
The agreement will enter into force 30 days after the two sides
have notified each other in writing that their respective
requirements for the entry into force of the agreement have been
complied with. 
</P>
</TEXT>
