<HEADLINE> Largest Cargo Service Station at Beijing Airport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 3 (Xinhua) -- A new cargo service station at
the Capital International Airport went into operation today,
possessing the country's largest annual handling capacity.
</P>
<P>
The fully-automated station, which is part of the airport's new
terminal building, cost a total 250 million yuan (30 million US
dollars).
</P>
<P>
The station covers an area of 135,200 square meters, and has a
designed handling capacity of 160,000 tons a year. It can handle
cargo from three airplanes simultaneously. 
