<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin on China's Good-Neighborliness </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 3 (Xinhua) -- China's modernization drive
calls for a long-term peaceful international environment and a
good surrounding environment, President Jiang Zemin said in
Bangkok today.
</P>
<P>
The stability and development in China, the peace and
prosperity in its surrounding areas, and a new regional security
order based on the Five Principles of Peaceful Coexistence, are
where the common interests of Asian countries and the fundamental
interests of China lie, he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, who arrived Thursday afternoon for a state visit, said
this during a speech entitled "Enhance Good-Neighborliness and
Friendship and Build a Better Future Together" at the National
Cultural Center of Thailand.
</P>
<P>
He said, "China firmly opposes hegemonism and power politics
and will never seek hegemony -- that is a solemn commitment that
the Chinese government and people have made to the whole world."
</P>
<P>
He said China pursues an independent foreign policy of peace
and a defense policy of a defensive nature, saying a developed
China will pose no threat to any country, and it will only be
conducive to regional and world peace and prosperity.
</P>
<P>
Even when China becomes more developed in the future, Jiang
said, it will continue to pursue an independent foreign policy of
peace and will stand firmly together with all other developing
countries and all peace-loving countries and peoples.
</P>
<P>
In the new century, the Chinese people will stand ready to work
together with the people of Thailand, ASEAN, Asia and other
countries in the world for the lofty cause of peace and
development in Asia and in the world at large.
</P>
<P>
On China's reunification cause, Jiang said that to keep the
nation unified has always been the main stream in China's history
and a lofty goal that the Chinese people have cherished from
generation to generation.
</P>
<P>
He said, "There is but one China in the world and Taiwan is an
inalienable part of Chinese territory. To solve the Taiwan
question in accordance with the basic principles of 'peaceful
reunification' and 'one country, two systems,' represents the
common aspiration of the entire Chinese people and the
overwhelming historical trend of China's development.
</P>
<P>
The situation in Hong Kong, since its return to China, has
shown that China's complete reunification is conducive to Asia's
stability and prosperity, Jiang added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
