<HEADLINE> China Sets Up Nuclear Insurance Community </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The China Nuclear Insurance
Community (CNIC) was set up here today, indicating deeper
cooperation in the country's high risk insurance community.
</P>
<P>
The nuclear insurance group consists of the China Reinsurance
Company, the People's Insurance Company of China, the China
Pacific Insurance Company, the China Ping'an Insurance Company,
and the Huatai Insurance Company.
</P>
<P>
According to Dai Fengju, chairman of the CNIC, the various
insurance companies within the community will share risks and
losses, which will provide insurance and guarantees to the fullest
extent for the country's nuclear power development.
</P>
<P>
Dai said that the services of the nuclear insurance community
include loss and liability insurance concerning nuclear power
stations within the border of China as well as other commercial
and civilian nuclear facilities.
</P>
<P>
Nuclear power plants demand higher safety standards than
facilities in other sectors. The Daya Bay Nuclear Power Plant in
south China's Shenzhen City, for instance, was insured at 1.4
billion U.S. dollars for property -- a cost which could not be
borne by any single insurance company.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
