<DOCNO> XIE19990903.0526 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tibetant Antelope Poacher Given Six-year Term </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'NING, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Wang Baobao, charged with
poaching 105 Tibetan antelopes at the Hoh Xil Nature Reserve in
northwest China's Qinghai Province, has been sentenced to six
years in jail.
</P>
<P>
Wang was nabbed by rangers at the reserve on April 12, during a
tough national anti-poaching campaign. Two accomplices remain at
large and are wanted by police.
</P>
<P>
The reserve, located on the Qinghai-Tibet Plateau, is home to
more than 20 rare species under State protection, including yak
and Tibetan antelope.
</P>
<P>
The number of poaching and smuggling cases of Tibetan antelope,
yak, and snow leopards, which have valuable fur, has increased in
recent years. Chinese forest police have launched the largest ever
anti-poaching endeavor called the "Hoh Xil No. 1 Action" since
April this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
