<HEADLINE> Malaysia's Top Pair Cut from Asian Badminton Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The Badminton Association
of Malaysia (BAM) Friday decided to leave out the current top pair
Choong Tan Fook and Lee Wan Wah from the national squad for the
19th Asian Championships to be held here from September 15 to 19.
</P>
<P>
The BAM selection committee decided to cut the pair from the
national squad for the tournament, Malaysia's official news agency
Bernama reported quoting BAM honorary secretary Mohammed Al-Amin
Abdul Majid.
</P>
<P>
The 14th-ranked Tan Fook-Wan Wah, who won the Konica Cup in
Singapore last week and did not compete in the ongoing Indonesian
Open in Bali, have been rested again for the 136,000 U.S. dollars
four-star event, he said.
</P>
<P>
"We think that Tan Fook and Wan Wah are in a good position to
qualify for the Sydney Olympics next year, so we selected several
other pairs to give them the chance to qualify too," the official
was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Malaysian squad to the forthcoming Championships:
</P>
<P>
Men's singles: Ong Ewe Hock, Rashid Sidek, Yong Hock Kin,
Roslin Hashim, James Chua, Jason Wong.
