<HEADLINE> Diplomats Visit Chinese Cultural Relics Show </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 3 (Xinhua) -- More than 60 foreign
diplomatic envoys in China today visited an exhibition of the
country's archaeological discoveries of the past 50 years at the
Chinese History Museum.
</P>
<P>
Today's activity, which was sponsored by the State
Administration of Cultural Heritage (SACH), was meant to foreign
diplomatic envoys the opportunity to know more about China's
cultural relics and its archaeological achievements since 1949
when New China was founded, said an official from the SACH.
</P>
<P>
He said that the visitors included Spanish, Mongolian, Peruvian,
Brazilian and Chilean ambassadors to China and diplomatic envoys
from other foreign embassies and consulates in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Some 450 cultural relics are on display at the exhibition,
which opened on August 13. 
</P>
