<HEADLINE> Pak Decides to Release Two Captured Indian Soldiers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The Pakistani government has
decided to immediately release the two Indian soldiers captured by
the Pakistani Army early this week.
</P>
<P>
The two Indian soldiers were captured during an attack by the
Indian troops on a Pakistani post in the Shyok-Turtok sector of
the disputed Kashmir on August 30.
</P>
<P>
The Pakistani Foreign Office said in a press release Friday
that the government has asked the International Committee of the
Red Cross (ICRC) to make appropriate arrangements for receiving
these two Indian soldiers and handing them over to the Indian
authorities.
</P>
<P>
The ICRC is taking appropriate action concerning the matter,
the press release said. 
</P>
