<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Qian Qichen Writes Preface for Book "Return of Macao" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The three-volume "Return of
Macao," with a preface by China's Vice-Premier Qian Qichen, has
been published by the Xinhua Publishing House.
</P>
<P>
The preface says that the Chinese government will resume the
exercise of sovereignty over Macao on December 20 this year, and
that Macao will become a special administrative region of the
People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
It goes on to say that the return of Macao to the motherland
will put an end to over 400 years of humiliation suffered by the
Chinese nation, signaling a further step forward toward
reunification of the motherland.
</P>
<P>
And it hails the return of Macao, another great event following
the return of Hong Kong to the motherland on July 1, 1997.
</P>
<P>
The vice-premier says in his preface that the State Council
appointed the first Chief Executive of the Macao Special
Administrative Region this May, which marks the start of "Macao
people governing Macao."
</P>
<P>
The preface says that "peaceful reunification" and "one country,
two systems" are consistent policies of the Chinese government.
With the "one China" principle, the great cause of reunifying the
motherland is bound to succeed, with the joint efforts of the
Chinese at home and abroad.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
