<HEADLINE> Karachi Stock Index Down for Second Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The Karachi Stock Exchange
(KSE)-100 index plunged for the second day Friday due to selling
all Scripps on the eve of Saturday's general strike.
</P>
<P>
The KSE-100 index closed 18.48 points, or 1.56 percent lower to
1166.40 against Thursday's 1184.88 points.
</P>
<P>
The total volume traded Friday stood at 150.848 million shares
against 184.649 million shares the previous day.
</P>
<P>
Of the 170 active issues, losers beat gainers 90 to 34 while 46
remained unchanged. 
</P>
