<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Stresses ASEAN's Role in Asian Peace, Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 3 (Xinhua) -- A united and prosperous ASEAN
(Association of Southeast Asian Nations) is an important force for
peace and development in Asia, Chinese President Jiang Zemin said
here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
He said, "We have the reason to believe that so long as the
Five Principles of Peaceful Coexistence are adhered to, there is a
bright prospect for the development of friendly relations between
China and ASEAN.
</P>
<P>
"China and ASEAN countries should always be good neighbors,
good friends and good partners," the Chinese president noted.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, who arrived Thursday afternoon on a state visit, made
the remarks in a speech entitled "Enhance Good-Neighbourliness and
Friendship and Build a Better Future Together" at the National
Cultural Center of Thailand.
</P>
<P>
Both China and ASEAN countries are advocates for a new
international order, he said, adding "Our consensus on strategic
issues is increasing."
</P>
<P>
He said, "Both China and ASEAN countries need to maintain good-
neighborliness and friendship with each other. So long as we
always try to resort to friendly consultation, there is no dispute
that cannot be solved."
</P>
<P>
In the course of the Asian financial crisis, Jiang went on to
say, China shared the difficulties of Thailand and other ASEAN
countries, went through thick and thin together with them, and
provided assistance within its capacity to the affected countries.
</P>
<P>
"China is ready to have in-depth discussions with the relevant
ASEAN countries on the principles and ways of safeguarding peace
and stability in this region as well as in the South China Sea. It
stands for the settlement of existing differences through friendly
consultation and negotiation," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
