<BODY>
<HEADLINE> MQM Stages Anti-Government Rally in Karachi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Hundreds of activists of the
ethnic Mohajir Qaumi Movement (MQM) Friday staged an
anti-government rally in a tense area of Pakistan's commercial
nerve center of Karachi.
</P>
<P>
MQM workers waving their party flags in the densely-populated
Burns road overcame the barricades erected by the security forces
to prevent the planned rally, sources from Karachi said.
</P>
<P>
Police fired in the air and used batons to prevent the MQM
demonstrators from entering the rally site in Burns road area.
However, about 400 activists managed to break the siege.
</P>
<P>
Thousands of policemen and other security personnel ringed the
venue for the protest rally. The security forces were seen
patrolling the area in armored vehicles and commandeered buses.
</P>
<P>
Hours before the rally, the police shot dead two MQM activists
in the city and sealed the city center to prevent the planned
anti-government rally.
</P>
<P>
MQM had been a coalition partner of the ruling Pakistan Muslim
League until a year ago when Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif parted
ways with the group for its alleged involvement in the murder of
former provincial governor Hakim Saeed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
