<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Two World Records Fall at Asian Weightlifting Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, CHINA, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Two world records fell at
the hands of Chinese strongwoman Lin Weining in the 69kg category
of the Asian Weightlifting Championships here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The 20-year-old Lin roared the world record at her third
attempt with a jerk of 142.5 kilograms which gave her another
world mark for a total of 252.5kg.
</P>
<P>
"I exploded my personal-best of 142.5kg in the jerk, but I was
a little bit upset for not shattering the snatch world record,"
Lin said.
</P>
<P>
Lin's junior compatriot Zhao Nan lifted 138.0kg for a new world
record, 0.5kg heavier than the previous weight set by Lin at the
World Youth Weightlifting Championships in Savannah, United States
in July before Lin snatched 138.5kg at her second attempt.
</P>
<P>
However, Lin snapped Zhao's delight by lifting 138.5kg at her
second attempt before she added the bar to 142.5kg.
</P>
<P>
"I always set my target to break the world record as heavy as
possible," Lin said.
</P>
<P>
Huang Hsi-Li from Chinese Taipei won the silver medal with a
total of 230.kg and Kageyama Miya of Japan place third for 177.5kg.
</P>
<P>
Shahin Nassirinia of Iran swept three titles in the men's 85kg
class with a snatch of 170.0, a jerk of 200.0 and a total of 370.
0kg,followed by his compatriot Hassan Pasham 342.5kg.
</P>
<P>
"My coach and I were confident to break the snatch world record
of 180.0kg at the World Weightlifting Championships in Athens,
Greece on November," said Nassirinia after failing to lift 180.5kg
at his third attempt.
</P>
<P>
The competitions of the women's 75kg and men's 94kg categories
will be contested tomorrow.  
</P>
</TEXT>
