<DOCNO> XIE19990903.0551 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Current Account Registers Surplus In 2nd Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The European Union's (EU)
current account registered a surplus of 3.5 billion euros (3.68
billion U.S. dollars) in the second quarter of 1999, the EU
statistics office, Eurostat, said on Friday.
</P>
<P>
This figure showed a remarkable drop from a surplus of 14.9
billion euros (15.65 billion U.S. dollars) in the same period in
1998.
</P>
<P>
The EU current account in the first quarter of 1999 registered
a deficit of 2.2 billion euros (2.3 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The Eurostat also said the service sector registered 2.4
billion euros (2.52 billion U.S. dollars) for trade in the second
quarter of 1999. The external trade balance was lower than that of
a surplus of 4.3 billion euros (4.52 billion U.S. dollars) in the
second quarter of 1998.
</P>
<P>
In the first quarter of this year, the 15-country bloc's
external balance of trade in service was in a deficit of 0.1
billion euros (0.105 billion U.S. dollars), the Eurostat report
indicated. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
