<HEADLINE> At Least Four Killed in U.S. Small Plane Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 3 (Xinhua) -- At least four people were
killed as an ambulance plane crashed in Florida, United States,
Friday morning, reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
All the dead were aboard the twin-engine plane. It wasn't
immediately known if any were patients.
</P>
<P>
The plane, which took off from a small airport near Pontiac,
Michigan, was diverted after the pilot reported problems, the
reports said.
</P>
<P>
The pilot asked permission to land at West Palm Beach. After
hitting the roof of a mall building just outside the airport, it
went through power lines and crashed onto the edge of airport
property, bursting into flames. 
