<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Eight People Killed in Plane Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 3 (Xinhua) - Eight people were killed and
three others injured after their light aircraft crashed Friday
near Glasgow Airport.
</P>
<P>
The twin-engine Cessna aircraft had just taken off from the
airport en route to Aberdeen when it came down in fields near
Paisley, Scotland.
</P>
<P>
A report from the scene said the aircraft skipped over a clump
of trees and nose dived into a field of rhubarb and burst into
flames on impact.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the Civil Aviation Authority said it was
believed the aircraft belonged to Edinburgh Air Charter. It is
thought to have been carrying a cabin crew from holiday tour
company called Airtours.
</P>
<P>
Scottish Secretary John Reid said Prime Minister Tony Blair,
who is on a visit to Scotland, was being kept fully informed of
the incident and Transport Minister Lord Macdonald was traveling
to the scene with air accident investigators. 
</P>
</TEXT>
