<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Robson Confirmed as Newcastle United New Manager </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Bobby Robson has been confirmed
as the new manager of Newcastle United, promising to turn around
the fortunes of the club he supported as a boy.
</P>
<P>
The 66-year-old England former boss said he was not under-
estimating the size of the challenge facing him at St James' Park
but said he was not afraid of it.
</P>
<P>
"I have got a massive job ahead of me. It's a great challenge
and I am up for it. There is no need for panic here."
</P>
<P>
Chairman Freddie Shepherd introduced Robson to a packed news
conference saying his first priority was to improve results -
Newcastle have not won a game since April.
</P>
<P>
But he said Robson, who has only signed a contract until the
end of the season, will also undertake a thorough review of all
aspects of the playing side.
</P>
<P>
Robson replaces Dutchman Ruud Gullit, who quit the Magpies last
Saturday after one of the worst starts to the season in the club's
history. Newcastle have only one point from six games in the
Premiership.
</P>
<P>
Robson said he had no immediate plans to bring in his own
deputy to replace Steve Clarke, the second-in-command appointed by
Gullit.
</P>
<P>
He said he had dreamed about managing Newcastle since he
watched the team as a boy in the 1950s but thought his chance had
gone when he turned the job down while manager of Barcelona.
</P>
<P>
"I thought Barcelona was a big club but I think this has just
pipped that."
</P>
<P>
He was courted for the top job at St James' Park during his
time in charge of the Spanish giants.
</P>
<P>
But he refused to break his contract and the job passed to
Kenny Dalglish.
</P>
<P>
Robson has not managed an English club side since leaving
Ipswich in 1982 to take over as England manager.
</P>
<P>
The oldest manager in the Premiership, Robson instead found
success at clubs in Portugal, the Netherlands and Spain.
</P>
<P>
Skipper Alan Shearer, whose breakdown in relations with Gullit
was one of the factors in the Dutchman's decision to quit,
welcomed his new boss.
</P>
<P>
"I have never had the privilege of playing for Bobby Robson,
but it is obvious from his track record that he is an outstanding
achiever with vast experience of football at every level.
</P>
<P>
"He also has local roots and will understand and share the
passion of our magnificent fans. I am looking forward to playing
for him," said the star football player. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
