<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tour of Spain Changes Jersey Color </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Organizers of the Tour of Spain
said that leader will no longer wear a yellow jersey, ending a 64-
year-old tradition that began in 1935.
</P>
<P>
"It will now be known as the 'golden jersey' and be a much
deeper color," Tour organizer Enrique Franco said in Murcia of
Spain on the eve of the race on Friday.
</P>
<P>
"We are entering a new millennium and it is a good time to
change the image of the Tour," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
